Black Jack Game

Game will have a computer dealer and a human player
We start with a normal deck of cards
The player can stand or hit
The player must be able to pick their betting amount
You need to keep track of player's total money
You need alert the player of wins, losses or busts etc.

Face Cards (Jack, Queen, King) count as a value of 10
Aces can count as either 1 or 11 whichever value is preferable to the player

----------------------------------------------------------------------------
GAME PLAY

1. Create a deck of 52 cards.
2. Shuffle the deck.
3. Ask the player of their bet.
4. Make sure that the player's bet doesn't exceed their available chips.
5. Deal two cards to the dealer and two cards to the player.
6. Show only one of the Dealer's cards, the other remain hidden
7. Show both of the player's cards
8. Ask the player if they wish to Hit, or take another card
9. If the player's hand doesn't bust (go over 21), ask if they'd like to Hit again
10. If a player Stands, play the Dealer's hand. The dealer will always Hit until the Dealer's
    value meets of exceeds 17
11. Determine the winner and adjust player's chips accordingly
12. Ask the player if they'd like to play again